WEBVTT

00:04.569 --> 00:06.702
- Previously
on "Good Girls"...

00:06.745 --> 00:08.095
- Are we going
to lose this house?

00:08.138 --> 00:09.357
- I mean, I don't know.

00:09.400 --> 00:11.446
- Nancy and I are suing you
for custody.

00:11.489 --> 00:13.361
- I would suggest
that we put Sara

00:13.404 --> 00:14.797
on a list
for a transplant.

00:14.840 --> 00:17.017
- How much is in the vault?
- 30 grand.

00:17.060 --> 00:18.583
- So when do you want
to do this?

00:18.627 --> 00:21.499
- Ladies and gentlemen,
this is a robbery.

00:21.543 --> 00:23.371
- Why does a grocery store
even have this kind of money?

00:23.414 --> 00:25.068
- Because it's hella shady!

00:25.112 --> 00:26.722
- Why don't you stop worrying
about my business

00:26.765 --> 00:28.680
and start figuring how you
gonna pay me my money back?

00:28.724 --> 00:30.160
- We have
a business proposition

00:30.204 --> 00:31.596
to clean your fake money.

00:31.640 --> 00:33.772
Let us do it right here.

00:33.816 --> 00:35.513
Fake money in,
real money out.

00:35.557 --> 00:36.688
- Do you want all this back
on the card?

00:36.732 --> 00:38.212
- Cash is fine.

00:38.255 --> 00:39.691
You want to bring other people
into this now?

00:39.735 --> 00:41.432
- The more you buy and return,

00:41.476 --> 00:43.086
the more money
you're going to make.

00:43.130 --> 00:44.827
- I don't know what
you've gotten me involved in,

00:44.870 --> 00:47.047
but it's something
super shady.

00:47.090 --> 00:50.180
- She's extorting us
to tune of $10,000!

00:50.224 --> 00:51.529
- Annie...
I mean, girls like that--

00:51.573 --> 00:53.096
they want
that kind of attention.

00:53.140 --> 00:54.445
- Is that why you tried
to rape her?

00:54.489 --> 00:56.099
- No!

00:56.143 --> 00:58.362
I saw this guy. Whatever
they're into, he's involved.

00:58.406 --> 01:00.060
- I'm just wondering where
a nice lady like you

01:00.103 --> 01:01.496
meets an inner-city gangbanger.

01:01.539 --> 01:03.106
- Maybe we should turn
ourselves in.

01:03.150 --> 01:05.543
- He's the one
who should be in jail, not us.

01:05.587 --> 01:07.458
- All we have to do
is get the vault open,

01:07.502 --> 01:08.677
and the cops will do
the rest.

01:08.720 --> 01:10.331
- Annie,
put all that money back now.

01:10.374 --> 01:12.202
- There has to be something
that you want.

01:12.246 --> 01:14.552
- The Feds and the DPD took
his gang down last night

01:14.596 --> 01:17.599
because these two women robbed
the place a couple nights ago.

01:18.904 --> 01:20.558
- I did it for us.
- I'm a cop.

01:20.602 --> 01:22.082
What the hell
am I supposed to do?

01:22.125 --> 01:23.561
- Sadie needs you, too.

01:23.605 --> 01:25.302
- That is exactly
what I needed to hear.

01:25.346 --> 01:26.564
- We just did in two seconds

01:26.608 --> 01:28.523
what they pay lawyers
for in blood.

01:28.566 --> 01:29.785
- Surprise.

01:29.828 --> 01:31.743
You're trying to put me away
and all,

01:31.787 --> 01:33.571
you must got big plans.

01:44.278 --> 01:46.715
- ♪ Breathing in the dark

01:46.758 --> 01:49.587
♪ Lying on its side

01:51.633 --> 01:54.114
- Oh, my God.
What happened?

01:54.157 --> 01:56.377
- Uh, hi. Hi.

01:56.420 --> 01:59.771
- Who steals a stop sign?

01:59.815 --> 02:01.817
- Oh. I know.

02:01.860 --> 02:04.124
- Stupid kids.

02:04.167 --> 02:05.473
- Not mine, thank God.

02:05.516 --> 02:08.650
Yours are angels.

02:08.693 --> 02:11.348
- That's a strong word, Elaine.

02:11.392 --> 02:13.916
- Which one made
a mess this time?

02:13.959 --> 02:15.439
- Me.

02:19.704 --> 02:21.445
- ♪ Oh

02:21.489 --> 02:23.621
♪ Forgiving who you are

02:23.665 --> 02:26.233
♪ For what you stand to gain

02:26.276 --> 02:31.194
♪ Just know that if you hide,
it doesn't go away ♪

02:31.238 --> 02:34.893
♪ When you get out of bed,
don't end up stranded ♪

02:34.937 --> 02:37.374
♪ Horrified with each stone

02:37.418 --> 02:40.377
♪ On the stage,
my little dark age ♪

02:54.696 --> 02:57.220
♪ All alone, open-eyed

02:57.264 --> 03:00.658
♪ Burn the page,
my little dark age ♪

03:03.270 --> 03:06.925
- Juan y María
van a la playa.

03:06.969 --> 03:08.753
- Juan and Maria
go to the pool.

03:08.797 --> 03:12.366
- Beach.

03:12.409 --> 03:14.890
- Ah, señora Cohen
would be so disappointed.

03:14.933 --> 03:17.240
- I heard she got hit
by a bus.

03:17.284 --> 03:18.807
- Autobus.

03:18.850 --> 03:20.417
- Greg...

03:20.461 --> 03:22.376
- No, I-I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
She was really cool.

03:22.419 --> 03:23.942
- No, no, it's--

03:23.986 --> 03:26.249
This is cheating.

03:26.293 --> 03:29.861
- No, no, it's not.
This is.

03:35.389 --> 03:38.609
- Oh, my God.
Why have you forsaken me?

03:38.653 --> 03:41.351
Ow! Greg!
- Oh, sorry. Sorry.

03:43.919 --> 03:45.573
We were doing so good.

03:45.616 --> 03:47.401
- I know. I know.

03:47.444 --> 03:49.968
- We were, like,
for-real adulting.

03:50.012 --> 03:51.709
- Yeah, but,
you know, the thing is

03:51.753 --> 03:54.277
that we got, like,
a kid together.

03:54.321 --> 03:57.889
- So, what, it's like
a tricky gray area?

03:57.933 --> 04:00.022
- Kind of.

04:03.068 --> 04:05.506
- We're--we're
just hammered, right?

04:08.465 --> 04:11.555
- I'm not actually
that hammered.

04:11.599 --> 04:13.775
- I'm barely buzzed.

04:28.659 --> 04:30.879
- Harry's down.

04:32.750 --> 04:34.752
He was making a poster for Sara

04:34.796 --> 04:36.841
but got tired halfway through.

04:36.885 --> 04:39.453
It says "welcome ho."

04:39.496 --> 04:41.846
- Hand me those.

04:47.765 --> 04:49.419
- Really?

04:49.463 --> 04:51.639
- Oh, yeah.

04:54.598 --> 04:56.948
- Make sure you get up early
so he doesn't see you.

04:56.992 --> 04:58.602
- I'm not lying to my kids.

04:58.646 --> 05:00.604
- Okay.
- That's your M.O.

05:02.476 --> 05:03.781
- What do you want here, Ruby?

05:03.825 --> 05:06.349
Hmm? You want to act
like nothing's wrong?

05:06.393 --> 05:09.787
You want to cuddle?
You want to watch reality TV?

05:09.831 --> 05:11.789
Well, guess what, baby.
I'm living it.

05:11.833 --> 05:14.052
- Stan--
- No, the things you did...

05:14.096 --> 05:17.665
- We needed the money.
- Everybody needs money!

05:17.708 --> 05:20.798
Everybody,
but normal people--

05:20.842 --> 05:23.366
good people,
they don't do what you did.

05:23.410 --> 05:25.803
All those nights
you slept like a baby

05:25.847 --> 05:29.024
right next to me
with your shady lying ass.

05:29.067 --> 05:31.548
- A street gang
was going to kill us.

05:31.592 --> 05:32.680
- Well, then you come to me!

05:32.723 --> 05:35.117
- I didn't want
to involve you.

05:35.160 --> 05:37.424
- And here we are.

05:41.689 --> 05:43.386
- What are you doing?
- What?

05:43.430 --> 05:44.822
- Why are you doing that?

05:44.866 --> 05:46.389
- Because you and your
girlfriends thought

05:46.433 --> 05:48.696
you could put a gang away.

05:53.527 --> 05:55.137
They made bail.

06:01.578 --> 06:04.886
- Hey, honey. We're home.

06:08.716 --> 06:09.978
Come on, Beth.

06:11.545 --> 06:13.460
- I thought you wanted
to be me.

06:13.503 --> 06:14.852
I mean, that's
what all this is, right?

06:14.896 --> 06:16.071
You trying
to put me away and all,

06:16.114 --> 06:18.682
you must got big plans.

06:18.726 --> 06:21.729
But see, you didn't think
things all the way through.

06:23.165 --> 06:24.732
It takes balls
to do what I do.

06:24.775 --> 06:26.690
You want to be the king,
you got to kill the king.

06:26.734 --> 06:28.170
This stuff's medieval,
darling.

06:28.213 --> 06:29.867
Please don't do this.

06:29.911 --> 06:31.695
Please don't kill us.

06:31.739 --> 06:35.873
-  I ain't--
I ain't gonna kill nobody.

06:37.571 --> 06:38.920
You are.

06:50.105 --> 06:52.803
- So what you think?

06:52.847 --> 06:55.719
You got what it takes?

06:57.547 --> 06:59.027
- Do it, Beth.

06:59.070 --> 07:00.855
- Please shut up.

07:00.898 --> 07:03.684
- Just shoot him.
- Shut up!

07:07.252 --> 07:08.732
How do I know it's loaded?

07:08.776 --> 07:10.473
- Oh, you can tell
by the weight.

07:10.517 --> 07:12.519
You know,
a full clip adds a pound.

07:12.562 --> 07:13.955
- Or you could just pull
the trigger.

07:13.998 --> 07:15.565
- Dean, shut up!

07:17.524 --> 07:20.178
What are you doing?

07:20.222 --> 07:22.964
- Oh, you thought you could
skip this part, huh?

07:23.007 --> 07:26.837
See--see, that's--that's
your problem right there.

07:26.881 --> 07:28.926
You want to get down
in the dirt so bad,

07:28.970 --> 07:31.233
but you want to keep
your hands clean, huh?

07:31.276 --> 07:33.104
- Do it, Beth, please.

07:33.148 --> 07:34.932
- You sit back down.

07:34.976 --> 07:36.760
- Do it, Beth.
- Sit!

07:38.632 --> 07:41.591
- What are you doing, Beth?

07:41.635 --> 07:43.593
- What are you doing,
Elizabeth?

07:47.858 --> 07:50.600
I don't know.

07:50.644 --> 07:53.647
I just want it to be over.

07:53.690 --> 07:55.126
- Yeah?

08:01.524 --> 08:03.134
Okay.

08:03.178 --> 08:05.615
Let's end it.

08:05.659 --> 08:07.269
For real.

08:08.923 --> 08:11.795
- It's all right.
It's okay.

08:15.799 --> 08:17.714
You did your best.

08:32.207 --> 08:34.296
- Okay.

08:34.339 --> 08:37.212
Now we're good, darling.

08:52.270 --> 08:55.665
- ♪ Under the white chalk

08:55.709 --> 08:59.408
♪ Drawn on the blackboard

08:59.451 --> 09:03.281
♪ Under the X-ray

09:03.325 --> 09:06.371
♪ I'm just a vertebrate

09:06.415 --> 09:09.592
♪ Do that to me

09:19.471 --> 09:21.343
- Where'd you get that?

09:21.386 --> 09:22.692
- Mm.

09:22.736 --> 09:25.216
Off one of those
little carts.

09:26.696 --> 09:29.264
- That's for a patient.

09:29.307 --> 09:31.919
- The cafeteria
was closed.

09:31.962 --> 09:34.617
- You stole
a sick person's food.

09:34.661 --> 09:38.273
- The cafeteria was closed.

09:41.668 --> 09:43.713
Honey, you want to get up

09:43.757 --> 09:45.497
and stretch your legs
a little bit?

09:45.541 --> 09:49.458
- Mm, mm-hmm.
Time for a pee break.

09:52.548 --> 09:55.856
- Mm...

09:59.686 --> 10:01.078
- Okay.

10:01.122 --> 10:03.298
- I'm so--I'm sorry.

10:05.692 --> 10:09.521
Oh, my God.
I am so sorry.

10:09.565 --> 10:12.220
- Yeah, let's, uh--Oh, wait.
Are we laughing or crying?

10:12.263 --> 10:13.656
- I don't know.

10:13.700 --> 10:18.139
- Are you happy or sad?
- I don't know.

10:18.182 --> 10:21.621
It's just the idea
that, like--

10:21.664 --> 10:24.580
I couldn't shoot the person
that, by all accounts,

10:24.624 --> 10:25.755
deserved it--

10:25.799 --> 10:29.150
I mean,
the violent gang leader.

10:29.193 --> 10:33.371
And then there's just--poor
Dean, he's just sitting there.

10:33.415 --> 10:36.984
And then, like,
all of a sudden, like...

10:37.027 --> 10:39.595
I mean,
talk about a drive-by.

10:41.728 --> 10:44.295
A drive-by.
- Okay.

10:44.339 --> 10:46.297
- I guess that's
kind of funny.

10:47.821 --> 10:49.649
- Come on.

10:54.262 --> 10:57.004
I hope your loved ones
are okay.

10:57.047 --> 10:59.397
I do.

10:59.441 --> 11:01.182
- Mrs. Boland.

11:01.225 --> 11:03.445
- Present.

11:03.488 --> 11:06.187
- She's really upset.

11:06.230 --> 11:08.363
- Your husband is going
to be fine.

11:08.406 --> 11:09.712
Another half inch
to the right,

11:09.756 --> 11:11.366
the bullet would've nicked
his aorta.

11:11.409 --> 11:13.237
We'd be having
a very different conversation.

11:13.281 --> 11:15.239
- Wait.
He's not dead?

11:15.283 --> 11:18.286
- No, he has a long road ahead,
but his--his vitals are stable.

11:27.643 --> 11:30.428
- I didn't kill my husband.

11:31.386 --> 11:33.518
- Yay.

11:33.562 --> 11:36.565
- Look at that.
- So good.

11:39.263 --> 11:41.396
- He's going to kill me.

11:46.314 --> 11:48.098
- Talk to me.
What do we got?

11:48.142 --> 11:51.319
- Um, a green bean.
Could be edamame.

11:51.362 --> 11:53.321
- Bag it.

11:53.364 --> 11:55.758
- Ooh, and a--and a pacifier.

11:58.239 --> 11:59.631
- Bag it, tag it.

12:02.286 --> 12:04.245
- The cops already
did this, Leslie.

12:13.602 --> 12:16.170
- I don't know what
those girls promised you

12:16.213 --> 12:18.520
or how much you got paid,

12:18.563 --> 12:20.652
but we both know
you sold out here...

12:20.696 --> 12:22.263
big-time.

12:22.306 --> 12:23.873
Got it?

12:23.917 --> 12:25.745
- Y-yes, Mr. Peterson.

12:27.616 --> 12:29.531
- Now get back down there
and find me some justice.

12:29.574 --> 12:32.621
- Y-yes. I'm on it,
Mr. Peterson.

12:32.664 --> 12:34.579
- Hey, hey!

12:34.623 --> 12:36.494
This is a crime scene.

12:36.538 --> 12:38.627
Behind the line.

12:49.159 --> 12:50.682
- Are you kidding me, man?

12:50.726 --> 12:52.423
- How you been, Jimmy?

12:52.467 --> 12:54.686
- Do you know what time it is?
- Who is it?

12:54.730 --> 12:57.820
- It's a work thing.
I got it.

12:57.864 --> 13:00.127
- Didn't know you had
a roommate.

13:00.170 --> 13:01.824
- What are you doing here?

13:01.868 --> 13:06.655
- You might want to round up
your team ASAP

13:06.698 --> 13:09.832
and let them know
they missed some stuff.

13:12.966 --> 13:14.924
It's just I watch
"The First 48," so I know--

13:14.968 --> 13:16.839
- You don't show up at my home
like a crazy person

13:16.883 --> 13:17.884
unless you're a crazy person.

13:17.927 --> 13:20.321
Are you crazy, Leslie?
Huh?

13:20.364 --> 13:21.844
'Cause if you are,
things are going to go down

13:21.888 --> 13:23.498
a whole lot differently.

13:23.541 --> 13:25.674
I'm not going to be
so reasonable. You feel me?

13:30.548 --> 13:32.812
Those girls--
they are playing you.

13:32.855 --> 13:35.510
They are right under your nose
laughing their asses off.

13:35.553 --> 13:37.555
- Get out of here.

14:01.928 --> 14:04.408
- ♪ Yeah, I been

14:04.452 --> 14:06.367
♪ Yeah

14:06.410 --> 14:09.283
♪ I been taking long,
I been writing songs ♪

14:09.326 --> 14:12.590
♪ I been feeling gone,
don't know what you want ♪

14:14.549 --> 14:15.855
- Time to take
your pills.

14:15.898 --> 14:18.553
- No, please, no.
- Yes, please, yes.

14:18.596 --> 14:19.946
- Hey, little people.

14:19.989 --> 14:22.470
- Hey.
- Hey.

14:22.513 --> 14:25.603
- Hey, how was your day?

14:25.647 --> 14:28.389
- Hey, how did Uncle Dean
get shot?

14:28.432 --> 14:32.915
- Uh, He was downtown late at
night, and someone robbed him.

14:32.959 --> 14:35.744
- Did you know the guy?
- No. Absolutely not.

14:35.787 --> 14:37.572
It was completely random.

14:37.615 --> 14:38.878
I mean, honestly,

14:38.921 --> 14:40.531
these things kind of happen
all the time.

14:40.575 --> 14:42.403
- They do?
- Well, I mean--

14:42.446 --> 14:45.972
I mean,
not all the time, no.

14:46.015 --> 14:48.757
But, I mean,
you never know.

14:48.800 --> 14:50.759
- What'd they take?

14:50.802 --> 14:52.456
- Nothing.

14:52.500 --> 14:53.849
- You just said he got robbed.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.938
- Take your pills, woman.
Take your pills.

14:55.982 --> 14:57.722
- Fine.

15:01.726 --> 15:03.641
- Who wants pizza?

15:03.685 --> 15:05.600
- What if it's the bad guy?

15:05.643 --> 15:07.471
- Bad guy don't ring doorbells.

15:07.515 --> 15:09.952
- ♪ Got it yelling,
got it yelling ♪

15:18.526 --> 15:20.441
- Hey.

15:22.617 --> 15:24.575
Have you had a week.

15:24.619 --> 15:27.535
Forensics found
a pen cap in the store.

15:27.578 --> 15:29.493
- What kind of pen?

15:29.537 --> 15:31.626
- The kind that matches
the ink on the envelope

15:31.669 --> 15:33.976
that you left for the Feds.

15:35.717 --> 15:38.763
- We were really careful.
- Oh, yeah? How careful?

15:38.807 --> 15:40.287
- Gloves and masks--

15:40.330 --> 15:43.986
- 'Cause there's
lipstick on it.

15:44.030 --> 15:46.032
- So just, like, be me
for a second, okay?

15:46.075 --> 15:47.947
I'm looking
over the list, right?

15:47.990 --> 15:52.647
Picture my damn face when
I see that you were a hostage

15:52.690 --> 15:55.519
in the very robbery
that took down the gangbanger

15:55.563 --> 15:58.479
that you had a little,
you know, uh...

15:58.522 --> 15:59.828
- Playdate.

15:59.871 --> 16:01.525
- Playdate with.

16:01.569 --> 16:03.310
What a small world.

16:03.353 --> 16:05.747
- I buy a lot of milk.
- Is that right?

16:05.790 --> 16:07.662
- It would be weird
if I wasn't there.

16:07.705 --> 16:11.579
- Mrs. Boland, I would love
for you to stop by the station.

16:11.622 --> 16:13.668
- I already gave my statement.

16:13.711 --> 16:16.845
- You did, but now I need
your DNA sample.

16:19.543 --> 16:21.545
- I think I'd like you
to leave.

16:22.720 --> 16:24.984
- That's probably a good idea.

16:27.377 --> 16:29.336
- And I'm calling a lawyer.

16:29.379 --> 16:31.077
- Even better.

16:48.746 --> 16:49.965
- You're going to go in there,

16:50.009 --> 16:51.706
and you're going
to give them everything.

16:51.749 --> 16:53.882
- You want me
to turn myself in?

16:53.925 --> 16:56.102
- I'll go with you.
- Why?

16:56.145 --> 16:57.929
- Because the first in
gets the best deal.

16:57.973 --> 16:59.844
Baby, that's the way it works.

16:59.888 --> 17:03.544
We'll be--Babe,
they don't care about you.

17:03.587 --> 17:05.024
They just want that gang,
you know?

17:05.067 --> 17:06.721
They just want to build
their case, right?

17:06.764 --> 17:08.984
So you go in there,
you tell them everything.

17:09.028 --> 17:10.986
You hear me? All of it.

17:11.030 --> 17:14.598
You tell them what you did,
how you did it...

17:16.600 --> 17:20.039
And who you did it with.
- You mean Beth and Annie?

17:21.779 --> 17:24.086
- Babe, they got DNA.

17:24.130 --> 17:25.870
This is over.

17:25.914 --> 17:27.568
- Beth was my maid of honor.
- Look, nobody said

17:27.611 --> 17:29.004
this was going to be pretty
and fair, Ruby.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.136
- I used to babysit Annie.

17:30.179 --> 17:32.094
- Excuse me,
you made this bed.

17:32.138 --> 17:34.705
- Oh, my God.
- And you made it well.

17:34.749 --> 17:36.664
I mean, it's got pillows,
it's got throws,

17:36.707 --> 17:38.100
it's got duvets in it.

17:38.144 --> 17:39.928
- Oh, my God, Stan.
- But you--but you did it

17:39.971 --> 17:41.669
for us, though, right?

17:41.712 --> 17:43.497
